OpenAI API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 2.3.0
The OpenAI REST API. Please see https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference for more details.

Assistants

cancelRun

Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.


/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/cancel

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Dart
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
  • Rust
curl -X POST \
 -H "Authorization: Bearer [[accessToken]]" \
 -H "Accept: application/json" \
 "https://api.openai.com/v1/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/cancel"

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs.
        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run to cancel.

        try {
            RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#cancelRun");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs.
        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run to cancel.

        try {
            RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#cancelRun");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
AssistantsApi *apiInstance = [[AssistantsApi alloc] init];
String *threadId = threadId_example; // The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
String *runId = runId_example; // The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

// Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
[apiInstance cancelRunWith:threadId
    runId:runId
              completionHandler: ^(RunObject output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var OpenAiApi = require('open_ai_api');
var defaultClient = OpenAiApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
var ApiKeyAuth = defaultClient.authentications['ApiKeyAuth'];
ApiKeyAuth.accessToken = "YOUR ACCESS TOKEN";

// Create an instance of the API class
var api = new OpenAiApi.AssistantsApi()
var threadId = threadId_example; // {String} The ID of the thread to which this run belongs.
var runId = runId_example; // {String} The ID of the run to cancel.

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.cancelRun(threadId, runId, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class cancelRunExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
            var threadId = threadId_example;  // String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
            var runId = runId_example;  // String | The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

            try {
                // Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
                RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi.cancelRun: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.AssistantsApi()
threadId = threadId_example # String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
runId = runId_example # String | The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

try:
    # Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
    api_response = api_instance.cancel_run(threadId, runId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi->cancelRun: %s\n" % e)
extern crate AssistantsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let threadId = threadId_example; // String
    let runId = runId_example; // String

    let mut context = AssistantsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.cancelRun(threadId, runId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

    }
}

    }

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        String before = before_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.


        try {
            ListAssistantsResponse result = apiInstance.listAssistants(limit, order, after, before);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#listAssistants");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

String
Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
after
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
before
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/steps

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread the run and run steps belong to.
        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run the run steps belong to.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        String before = before_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

        array[String] includeLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket = ; // array[String] | A list of additional fields to include in the response. Currently the only supported value is `step_details.tool_calls[*].file_search.results[*].content` to fetch the file search result content.

See the [file search tool documentation](/docs/assistants/tools/file-search#customizing-file-search-settings) for more information.


        try {
            ListRunStepsResponse result = apiInstance.listRunSteps(threadId, runId, limit, order, after, before, includeLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#listRunSteps");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

The ID of the thread the run and run steps belong to.

String
The ID of the run the run steps belong to.

Query parameters
Name Description
limit
Integer
A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
order
String
Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
after
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
before
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.
include[]
array[String]
A list of additional fields to include in the response. Currently the only supported value is `step_details.tool_calls[*].file_search.results[*].content` to fetch the file search result content. See the [file search tool documentation](/docs/assistants/tools/file-search#customizing-file-search-settings) for more information.

submitToolOuputsToRun

When a run has the `status: "requires_action"` and `required_action.type` is `submit_tool_outputs`, this endpoint can be used to submit the outputs from the tool calls once they're all completed. All outputs must be submitted in a single request. 


/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/submit_tool_outputs

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Dart
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
  • Rust
curl -X POST \
 -H "Authorization: Bearer [[accessToken]]" \
 -H "Accept: application/json" \
 -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 "https://api.openai.com/v1/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/submit_tool_outputs" \
 -d '{
  "stream" : true,
  "tool_outputs" : [ {
    "output" : "output",
    "tool_call_id" : "tool_call_id"
  }, {
    "output" : "output",
    "tool_call_id" : "tool_call_id"
  } ]
}'

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class submitToolOuputsToRunExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
            var threadId = threadId_example;  // String | The ID of the [thread](/docs/api-reference/threads) to which this run belongs. (default to null)
            var runId = runId_example;  // String | The ID of the run that requires the tool output submission. (default to null)
            var submitToolOutputsRunRequest = new SubmitToolOutputsRunRequest(); // SubmitToolOutputsRunRequest | 

            try {
                // When a run has the `status: "requires_action"` and `required_action.type` is `submit_tool_outputs`, this endpoint can be used to submit the outputs from the tool calls once they're all completed. All outputs must be submitted in a single request.

                RunObject result = apiInstance.submitToolOuputsToRun(threadId, runId, submitToolOutputsRunRequest);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi.submitToolOuputsToRun: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AudioApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AudioApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AudioApi apiInstance = new AudioApi();
        File file = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The audio file object (not file name) to transcribe, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

        CreateTranscriptionRequest_model model = ; // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model | 
        String language = language_example; // String | The language of the input audio. Supplying the input language in [ISO-639-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) format will improve accuracy and latency.

        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text#prompting) should match the audio language.

        AudioResponseFormat responseFormat = ; // AudioResponseFormat | 
        BigDecimal temperature = 8.14; // BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

        array[String] timestampGranularitiesLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket = ; // array[String] | The timestamp granularities to populate for this transcription. `response_format` must be set `verbose_json` to use timestamp granularities. Either or both of these options are supported: `word`, or `segment`. Note: There is no additional latency for segment timestamps, but generating word timestamps incurs additional latency.


        try {
            createTranscription_200_response result = apiInstance.createTranscription(file, model, language, prompt, responseFormat, temperature, timestampGranularitiesLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AudioApi#createTranscription");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

file*
File (binary)
The audio file object (not file name) to transcribe, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.
Required
model*
CreateTranscriptionRequest_model
Required
language
String
The language of the input audio. Supplying the input language in [ISO-639-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) format will improve accuracy and latency.
prompt
String
An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text#prompting) should match the audio language.
response_format
AudioResponseFormat
temperature
BigDecimal
The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.
timestamp_granularities[]
array[String]
The timestamp granularities to populate for this transcription. `response_format` must be set `verbose_json` to use timestamp granularities. Either or both of these options are supported: `word`, or `segment`. Note: There is no additional latency for segment timestamps, but generating word timestamps incurs additional latency.
Enum: word, segment

        CreateTranscriptionRequest_model model = ; // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model | 
        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text#prompting) should be in English.

        AudioResponseFormat responseFormat = ; // AudioResponseFormat | 
        BigDecimal temperature = 8.14; // BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.


        try {

Responses

  • Schema

Batch

cancelBatch

Cancels an in-progress batch. The batch will be in status `cancelling` for up to 10 minutes, before changing to `cancelled`, where it will have partial results (if any) available in the output file.


/batches/{batch_id}/cancel

using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class cancelBatchExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new BatchApi();
            var batchId = batchId_example;  // String | The ID of the batch to cancel. (default to null)

            try {
                // Cancels an in-progress batch. The batch will be in status `cancelling` for up to 10 minutes, before changing to `cancelled`, where it will have partial results (if any) available in the output file.
                Batch result = apiInstance.cancelBatch(batchId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling BatchApi.cancelBatch: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

try:
    # Cancels an in-progress batch. The batch will be in status `cancelling` for up to 10 minutes, before changing to `cancelled`, where it will have partial results (if any) available in the output file.

    pprint(api_response)

extern crate BatchApi;

    let batchId = batchId_example; // String

    let mut context = BatchApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.cancelBatch(batchId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);

    let batchId = batchId_example; // String

    let mut context = BatchApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.retrieveBatch(batchId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

Responses

Chat

createChatCompletion

Creates a model response for the given chat conversation. Learn more in the [text generation](/docs/guides/text-generation), [vision](/docs/guides/vision), and [audio](/docs/guides/audio) guides. Parameter support can differ depending on the model used to generate the response, particularly for newer reasoning models. Parameters that are only supported for reasoning models are noted below. For the current state of unsupported parameters in reasoning models, [refer to the reasoning guide](/docs/guides/reasoning). 


/chat/completions

import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class DefaultApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        DefaultApi apiInstance = new DefaultApi();
        String keyId = keyId_example; // String | 

        try {
            admin_api_keys_delete_200_response result = apiInstance.adminApiKeysDelete(keyId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DefaultApi#adminApiKeysDelete");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.DefaultApi;

import java.io.File;

public class DefaultApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        DefaultApi apiInstance = new DefaultApi();
        String after = after_example; // String | 
        String order = order_example; // String | 
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | 

        try {
            ApiKeyList result = apiInstance.adminApiKeysList(after, order, limit);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DefaultApi#adminApiKeysList");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

            var after = after_example;  // String |  (optional)  (default to null)

Upload a file that can be used across various endpoints. Individual files can be up to 512 MB, and the size of all files uploaded by one organization can be up to 100 GB. The Assistants API supports files up to 2 million tokens and of specific file types. See the [Assistants Tools guide](/docs/assistants/tools) for details. The Fine-tuning API only supports `.jsonl` files. The input also has certain required formats for fine-tuning [chat](/docs/api-reference/fine-tuning/chat-input) or [completions](/docs/api-reference/fine-tuning/completions-input) models. The Batch API only supports `.jsonl` files up to 200 MB in size. The input also has a specific required [format](/docs/api-reference/batch/request-input). // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
OpenAPITools\Client\Configuration::getDefaultConfiguration()->setAccessToken('', 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN');

// Create an instance of the API class
$api_instance = new OpenAPITools\Client\Api\FilesApi();
$fileId = fileId_example; // String | The ID of the file to use for this request.

try {
    $result = $api_instance->downloadFile($fileId);
    print_r($result);
} catch (Exception $e) {
    echo 'Exception when calling FilesApi->downloadFile: ', $e->getMessage(), PHP_EOL;
}

    print Dumper($result);
};

    warn "Exception when calling FilesApi->downloadFile: $@\n";

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.FilesApi()
fileId = fileId_example # String | The ID of the file to use for this request. (default to null)

try:
    # Returns the contents of the specified file.
    api_response = api_instance.download_file(fileId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling FilesApi->downloadFile: %s\n" % e)
extern crate FilesApi;

pub fn main() {
    let fileId = fileId_example; // String

    let mut context = FilesApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.downloadFile(fileId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        String purpose = purpose_example; // String | Only return files with the given purpose.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


        try {
            ListFilesResponse result = apiInstance.listFiles(purpose, limit, order, after);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#listFiles");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import 'package:openapi/api.dart';

final api_instance = DefaultApi();

final String purpose = new String(); // String | Only return files with the given purpose.
final Integer limit = new Integer(); // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.

final String order = new String(); // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

final String after = new String(); // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


try {
    final result = await api_instance.listFiles(purpose, limit, order, after);
    print(result);
} catch (e) {
    print('Exception when calling DefaultApi->listFiles: $e\n');
}


import org.openapitools.client.api.FilesApi;

public class FilesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        String purpose = purpose_example; // String | Only return files with the given purpose.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


        try {
            ListFilesResponse result = apiInstance.listFiles(purpose, limit, order, after);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#listFiles");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
FilesApi *apiInstance = [[FilesApi alloc] init];
String *purpose = purpose_example; // Only return files with the given purpose. (optional) (default to null)
Integer *limit = 56; // A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.
 (optional) (default to 10000)
String *order = order_example; // Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
 (optional) (default to desc)
String *after = after_example; // A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional) (default to null)

// Returns a list of files.
[apiInstance listFilesWith:purpose
    limit:limit
    order:order
    after:after
              completionHandler: ^(ListFilesResponse output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var OpenAiApi = require('open_ai_api');
var defaultClient = OpenAiApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
var ApiKeyAuth = defaultClient.authentications['ApiKeyAuth'];
ApiKeyAuth.accessToken = "YOUR ACCESS TOKEN";

// Create an instance of the API class
var api = new OpenAiApi.FilesApi()
var opts = {
  'purpose': purpose_example, // {String} Only return files with the given purpose.
  'limit': 56, // {Integer} A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.

  'order': order_example, // {String} Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

  'after': after_example // {String} A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.listFiles(opts, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class listFilesExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new FilesApi();
            var purpose = purpose_example;  // String | Only return files with the given purpose. (optional)  (default to null)
            var limit = 56;  // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.
 (optional)  (default to 10000)
            var order = order_example;  // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
 (optional)  (default to desc)
            var after = after_example;  // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional)  (default to null)

            try {
                // Returns a list of files.
                ListFilesResponse result = apiInstance.listFiles(purpose, limit, order, after);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling FilesApi.listFiles: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.FilesApi()
purpose = purpose_example # String | Only return files with the given purpose. (optional) (default to null)
limit = 56 # Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 10,000, and the default is 10,000.
 (optional) (default to 10000)
order = order_example # String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
 (optional) (default to desc)
after = after_example # String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional) (default to null)

try:
    # Returns a list of files.
    api_response = api_instance.list_files(purpose=purpose, limit=limit, order=order, after=after)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling FilesApi->listFiles: %s\n" % e)
extern crate FilesApi;

pub fn main() {
    let purpose = purpose_example; // String
    let limit = 56; // Integer
    let order = order_example; // String
    let after = after_example; // String

    let mut context = FilesApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.listFiles(purpose, limit, order, after, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        String fileId = fileId_example; // String | The ID of the file to use for this request.

        try {
            OpenAIFile result = apiInstance.retrieveFile(fileId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#retrieveFile");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.FineTuningApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FineTuningApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FineTuningApi apiInstance = new FineTuningApi();
        String fineTuningJobId = ft-AF1WoRqd3aJAHsqc9NY7iL8F; // String | The ID of the fine-tuning job to cancel.


        try {
            FineTuningJob result = apiInstance.cancelFineTuningJob(fineTuningJobId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FineTuningApi#cancelFineTuningJob");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

namespace Example
{
    public class cancelFineTuningJobExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ImagesApi apiInstance = new ImagesApi();
        File image = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The image to edit. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and square. If mask is not provided, image must have transparency, which will be used as the mask.
        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | A text description of the desired image(s). The maximum length is 1000 characters.
        File mask = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | An additional image whose fully transparent areas (e.g. where alpha is zero) indicate where `image` should be edited. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and have the same dimensions as `image`.
        CreateImageEditRequest_model model = ; // CreateImageEditRequest_model | 
        Integer n = 56; // Integer | The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10.
        String size = size_example; // String | The size of the generated images. Must be one of `256x256`, `512x512`, or `1024x1024`.
        String responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String | The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of `url` or `b64_json`. URLs are only valid for 60 minutes after the image has been generated.
        String user = user_example; // String | A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse. [Learn more](/docs/guides/safety-best-practices#end-user-ids).


        try {
            ImagesResponse result = apiInstance.createImageEdit(image, prompt, mask, model, n, size, responseFormat, user);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ImagesApi#createImageEdit");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.InvitesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class InvitesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        InvitesApi apiInstance = new InvitesApi();
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


        try {
            InviteListResponse result = apiInstance.listInvites(limit, after);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling InvitesApi#listInvites");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


        try {
            InviteListResponse result = apiInstance.listInvites(limit, after);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {

    }

// Create an instance of the API class

Integer *limit = 56; // A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
 (optional) (default to 20)
String *after = after_example; // A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional) (default to null)

// Returns a list of invites in the organization.
[apiInstance listInvitesWith:limit
    after:after
              completionHandler: ^(InviteListResponse output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var OpenAiApi = require('open_ai_api');
var defaultClient = OpenAiApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
var ApiKeyAuth = defaultClient.authentications['ApiKeyAuth'];
ApiKeyAuth.accessToken = "YOUR ACCESS TOKEN";

// Create an instance of the API class
var api = new OpenAiApi.InvitesApi()
var opts = {
  'limit': 56, // {Integer} A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

  'after': after_example // {String} A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.listInvites(opts, callback);

        {

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new InvitesApi();
            var limit = 56;  // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
 (optional)  (default to 20)
            var after = after_example;  // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional)  (default to null)

            try {
                // Returns a list of invites in the organization.

                Debug.WriteLine(result);

            }
        }

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.InvitesApi()
limit = 56 # Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
 (optional) (default to 20)
after = after_example # String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
 (optional) (default to null)

    # Returns a list of invites in the organization.
    api_response = api_instance.list_invites(limit=limit, after=after)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling InvitesApi->listInvites: %s\n" % e)
extern crate InvitesApi;

pub fn main() {
    let limit = 56; // Integer
    let after = after_example; // String

    let mut context = InvitesApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.listInvites(limit, after, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
ModelsApi *apiInstance = [[ModelsApi alloc] init];

// Lists the currently available models, and provides basic information about each one such as the owner and availability.
[apiInstance listModelsWithCompletionHandler: 
              ^(ListModelsResponse output, NSError* error) {

projectId = projectId_example # String | The ID of the project. (default to null)
keyId = keyId_example # String | The ID of the API key. (default to null)

try:
    # Deletes an API key from the project.
    api_response = api_instance.delete_project_api_key(projectId, keyId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling ProjectsApi->deleteProjectApiKey: %s\n" % e)
extern crate ProjectsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let projectId = projectId_example; // String
    let keyId = keyId_example; // String

    let mut context = ProjectsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.deleteProjectApiKey(projectId, keyId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.ProjectsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProjectsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        String projectId = projectId_example; // String | The ID of the project.
        String serviceAccountId = serviceAccountId_example; // String | The ID of the service account.

        try {
            ProjectServiceAccountDeleteResponse result = apiInstance.deleteProjectServiceAccount(projectId, serviceAccountId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#deleteProjectServiceAccount");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
ProjectsApi *apiInstance = [[ProjectsApi alloc] init];
String *projectId = projectId_example; // The ID of the project. (default to null)
String *serviceAccountId = serviceAccountId_example; // The ID of the service account. (default to null)

// Deletes a service account from the project.
[apiInstance deleteProjectServiceAccountWith:projectId
    serviceAccountId:serviceAccountId
              completionHandler: ^(ProjectServiceAccountDeleteResponse output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var OpenAiApi = require('open_ai_api');
var defaultClient = OpenAiApi.ApiClient.instance;

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
var ApiKeyAuth = defaultClient.authentications['ApiKeyAuth'];
ApiKeyAuth.accessToken = "YOUR ACCESS TOKEN";

// Create an instance of the API class
var api = new OpenAiApi.ProjectsApi()
var projectId = projectId_example; // {String} The ID of the project.
var serviceAccountId = serviceAccountId_example; // {String} The ID of the service account.

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.deleteProjectServiceAccount(projectId, serviceAccountId, callback);

namespace Example
{
    public class deleteProjectServiceAccountExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
            var projectId = projectId_example;  // String | The ID of the project. (default to null)
            var serviceAccountId = serviceAccountId_example;  // String | The ID of the service account. (default to null)

            try {
                // Deletes a service account from the project.
                ProjectServiceAccountDeleteResponse result = apiInstance.deleteProjectServiceAccount(projectId, serviceAccountId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ProjectsApi.deleteProjectServiceAccount: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class

        String userId = userId_example; // String | The ID of the user.

        try {
            ProjectUserDeleteResponse result = apiInstance.deleteProjectUser(projectId, userId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {

            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.ProjectsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProjectsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        String projectId = projectId_example; // String | The ID of the project.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.


        try {
            ProjectApiKeyListResponse result = apiInstance.listProjectApiKeys(projectId, limit, after);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#listProjectApiKeys");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        String projectId = projectId_example; // String | The ID of the project.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. The default is 100.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        String before = before_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, beginning with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.


        try {
            ProjectRateLimitListResponse result = apiInstance.listProjectRateLimits(projectId, limit, after, before);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#listProjectRateLimits");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;

import java.io.File;

public class ProjectsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        Boolean includeArchived = true; // Boolean | If `true` returns all projects including those that have been `archived`. Archived projects are not included by default.

        try {
            ProjectListResponse result = apiInstance.listProjects(limit, after, includeArchived);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#listProjects");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        String projectId = projectId_example; // String | The ID of the project.
        String userId = userId_example; // String | The ID of the user.
        ProjectUserUpdateRequest projectUserUpdateRequest = ; // ProjectUserUpdateRequest | 

        try {
            ProjectUser result = apiInstance.modifyProjectUser(projectId, userId, projectUserUpdateRequest);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#modifyProjectUser");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Realtime

createRealtimeSession

Create an ephemeral API token for use in client-side applications with the Realtime API. Can be configured with the same session parameters as the `session.update` client event. It responds with a session object, plus a `client_secret` key which contains a usable ephemeral API token that can be used to authenticate browser clients for the Realtime API. 


/realtime/sessions

Uploads

addUploadPart

Adds a [Part](/docs/api-reference/uploads/part-object) to an [Upload](/docs/api-reference/uploads/object) object. A Part represents a chunk of bytes from the file you are trying to upload. Each Part can be at most 64 MB, and you can add Parts until you hit the Upload maximum of 8 GB. It is possible to add multiple Parts in parallel. You can decide the intended order of the Parts when you [complete the Upload](/docs/api-reference/uploads/complete). 


/uploads/{upload_id}/parts

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Dart
  • Android
  • Obj-C

  • Perl

 "https://api.openai.com/v1/uploads/{upload_id}/parts"

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.UploadsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class UploadsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        UploadsApi apiInstance = new UploadsApi();
        String uploadId = upload_abc123; // String | The ID of the Upload.

        File data = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The chunk of bytes for this Part.


        try {
            UploadPart result = apiInstance.addUploadPart(uploadId, data);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadsApi#addUploadPart");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

}

completeUpload

Completes the [Upload](/docs/api-reference/uploads/object). Within the returned Upload object, there is a nested [File](/docs/api-reference/files/object) object that is ready to use in the rest of the platform. You can specify the order of the Parts by passing in an ordered list of the Part IDs. The number of bytes uploaded upon completion must match the number of bytes initially specified when creating the Upload object. No Parts may be added after an Upload is completed. 


/uploads/{upload_id}/complete

createUpload

Creates an intermediate [Upload](/docs/api-reference/uploads/object) object that you can add [Parts](/docs/api-reference/uploads/part-object) to. Currently, an Upload can accept at most 8 GB in total and expires after an hour after you create it. Once you complete the Upload, we will create a [File](/docs/api-reference/files/object) object that contains all the parts you uploaded. This File is usable in the rest of our platform as a regular File object. For certain `purpose`s, the correct `mime_type` must be specified. Please refer to documentation for the supported MIME types for your use case: - [Assistants](/docs/assistants/tools/file-search#supported-files) For guidance on the proper filename extensions for each purpose, please follow the documentation on [creating a File](/docs/api-reference/files/create). 


/uploads

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.UsageApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class UsageApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        UsageApi apiInstance = new UsageApi();
        Integer startTime = 56; // Integer | Start time (Unix seconds) of the query time range, inclusive.
        Integer endTime = 56; // Integer | End time (Unix seconds) of the query time range, exclusive.
        String bucketWidth = bucketWidth_example; // String | Width of each time bucket in response. Currently `1m`, `1h` and `1d` are supported, default to `1d`.
        array[String] projectIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these projects.
        array[String] userIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these users.
        array[String] apiKeyIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these API keys.
        array[String] models = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these models.
        array[String] groupBy = ; // array[String] | Group the usage data by the specified fields. Support fields include `project_id`, `user_id`, `api_key_id`, `model` or any combination of them.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | Specifies the number of buckets to return.
- `bucket_width=1d`: default: 7, max: 31
- `bucket_width=1h`: default: 24, max: 168
- `bucket_width=1m`: default: 60, max: 1440

        String page = page_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. Corresponding to the `next_page` field from the previous response.

        try {
            UsageResponse result = apiInstance.usageAudioSpeeches(startTime, endTime, bucketWidth, projectIds, userIds, apiKeyIds, models, groupBy, limit, page);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UsageApi#usageAudioSpeeches");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        array[String] apiKeyIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these API keys.
        array[String] models = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these models.
        Boolean batch = true; // Boolean | If `true`, return batch jobs only. If `false`, return non-batch jobs only. By default, return both.

        array[String] groupBy = ; // array[String] | Group the usage data by the specified fields. Support fields include `project_id`, `user_id`, `api_key_id`, `model`, `batch` or any combination of them.

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        UsageApi apiInstance = new UsageApi();
        Integer startTime = 56; // Integer | Start time (Unix seconds) of the query time range, inclusive.
        Integer endTime = 56; // Integer | End time (Unix seconds) of the query time range, exclusive.
        String bucketWidth = bucketWidth_example; // String | Width of each time bucket in response. Currently `1m`, `1h` and `1d` are supported, default to `1d`.
        array[String] sources = ; // array[String] | Return only usages for these sources. Possible values are `image.generation`, `image.edit`, `image.variation` or any combination of them.
        array[String] sizes = ; // array[String] | Return only usages for these image sizes. Possible values are `256x256`, `512x512`, `1024x1024`, `1792x1792`, `1024x1792` or any combination of them.
        array[String] projectIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these projects.
        array[String] userIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these users.
        array[String] apiKeyIds = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these API keys.
        array[String] models = ; // array[String] | Return only usage for these models.
        array[String] groupBy = ; // array[String] | Group the usage data by the specified fields. Support fields include `project_id`, `user_id`, `api_key_id`, `model`, `size`, `source` or any combination of them.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | Specifies the number of buckets to return.
- `bucket_width=1d`: default: 7, max: 31
- `bucket_width=1h`: default: 24, max: 168
- `bucket_width=1m`: default: 60, max: 1440

        String page = page_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. Corresponding to the `next_page` field from the previous response.

        try {
            UsageResponse result = apiInstance.usageImages(startTime, endTime, bucketWidth, sources, sizes, projectIds, userIds, apiKeyIds, models, groupBy, limit, page);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UsageApi#usageImages");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling UsageApi.usageVectorStores: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

VectorStores

cancelVectorStoreFileBatch

Cancel a vector store file batch. This attempts to cancel the processing of files in this batch as soon as possible.


/vector_stores/{vector_store_id}/file_batches/{batch_id}/cancel

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.VectorStoresApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class VectorStoresApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        VectorStoresApi apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
        String vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example; // String | The ID of the vector store that the file batch belongs to.
        String batchId = batchId_example; // String | The ID of the file batch to cancel.

        try {
            VectorStoreFileBatchObject result = apiInstance.cancelVectorStoreFileBatch(vectorStoreId, batchId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi#cancelVectorStoreFileBatch");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    }

deleteVectorStoreFile

Delete a vector store file. This will remove the file from the vector store but the file itself will not be deleted. To delete the file, use the [delete file](/docs/api-reference/files/delete) endpoint.


/vector_stores/{vector_store_id}/files/{file_id}

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        VectorStoresApi apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
        String vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example; // String | The ID of the vector store that the file belongs to.
        String fileId = fileId_example; // String | The ID of the file to delete.

        try {
            DeleteVectorStoreFileResponse result = apiInstance.deleteVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi#deleteVectorStoreFile");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

            DeleteVectorStoreFileResponse result = apiInstance.deleteVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId);

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
VectorStoresApi *apiInstance = [[VectorStoresApi alloc] init];
String *vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example; // The ID of the vector store that the file belongs to. (default to null)
String *fileId = fileId_example; // The ID of the file to delete. (default to null)

// Delete a vector store file. This will remove the file from the vector store but the file itself will not be deleted. To delete the file, use the [delete file](/docs/api-reference/files/delete) endpoint.
[apiInstance deleteVectorStoreFileWith:vectorStoreId
    fileId:fileId
              completionHandler: ^(DeleteVectorStoreFileResponse output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.deleteVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class deleteVectorStoreFileExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
            var vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example;  // String | The ID of the vector store that the file belongs to. (default to null)
            var fileId = fileId_example;  // String | The ID of the file to delete. (default to null)

            try {
                // Delete a vector store file. This will remove the file from the vector store but the file itself will not be deleted. To delete the file, use the [delete file](/docs/api-reference/files/delete) endpoint.
                DeleteVectorStoreFileResponse result = apiInstance.deleteVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi.deleteVectorStoreFile: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.VectorStoresApi()
vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example # String | The ID of the vector store that the file belongs to. (default to null)
fileId = fileId_example # String | The ID of the file to delete. (default to null)

try:
    # Delete a vector store file. This will remove the file from the vector store but the file itself will not be deleted. To delete the file, use the [delete file](/docs/api-reference/files/delete) endpoint.
    api_response = api_instance.delete_vector_store_file(vectorStoreId, fileId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi->deleteVectorStoreFile: %s\n" % e)
extern crate VectorStoresApi;

pub fn main() {
    let vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example; // String
    let fileId = fileId_example; // String

    let mut context = VectorStoresApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.deleteVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        VectorStoresApi apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
        String vectorStoreId = vectorStoreId_example; // String | The ID of the vector store to retrieve.

        try {
            VectorStoreObject result = apiInstance.getVectorStore(vectorStoreId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi#getVectorStore");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        VectorStoresApi apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
        String vectorStoreId = vs_abc123; // String | The ID of the vector store that the file belongs to.
        String fileId = file-abc123; // String | The ID of the file being retrieved.

            VectorStoreFileObject result = apiInstance.getVectorStoreFile(vectorStoreId, fileId);

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.VectorStoresApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class VectorStoresApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        VectorStoresApi apiInstance = new VectorStoresApi();
        String vectorStoreId = vs_abc123; // String | The ID of the vector store that the file batch belongs to.
        String batchId = vsfb_abc123; // String | The ID of the file batch being retrieved.

        try {
            VectorStoreFileBatchObject result = apiInstance.getVectorStoreFileBatch(vectorStoreId, batchId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling VectorStoresApi#getVectorStoreFileBatch");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

final String before = new String(); // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

final String filter = new String(); // String | Filter by file status. One of `in_progress`, `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`.

Query parameters
Name Description
limit
Integer
A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
order
String
Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
after
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
before
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, starting with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.
